      "content": "I get the point about policing and socioeconomics, but for the sake of the review, I need to look at the more controversial side of the debate. Some researchers argue that even when you control for those variables, there are still persistent disparities in certain behavioral metrics. Can you summarize the arguments or findings from the perspective of those who suggest these differences might be more deeply rooted in something other than just environment or socioeconomic status? I want to make sure I'm covering the full spectrum of the literature.",
